polish: translations + theme/picker dedup + optimistic send + live row

Fixes the issues called out after the first TestFlight build:

Translations (ru / uk / en) for every string added in Phase F + G:
Global, Find people, New direct chat, New group, Group chat,
Group info, Group name, Members, Name, Save, Create, Leave,
Leave group, Leave this group?, Add member, Add by username,
Type to search, Username (e.g. letychkauser...), Your global
username, No global chats yet, No messages yet, No one found.,
the long disclaimer text, etc. The old "in progress" hint is
kept so any iOS still showing it does not fall back to English.

Picker doubling: the Settings tab repeated the section header
inline as the Picker label (e.g. "Network mode" header + "Network
mode" picker label on the row). Added .labelsHidden() on the
three Pickers (Network mode, Language, Theme) so only the
section header is shown.

"Anon" was still hardcoded in one spot of the delete-account
flow; replaced with Ident.defaultNick so the nick field falls
back to letychkauser#xxx.

Global.sendText now uses insert.select().value so the server row
(with canonical id + created_at) is returned and appended to the
local messages immediately. Own bubble appears right away instead
of after the 2-second poll cycle.

GroupSettingsView and GlobalChatView now derive the row from
Global.shared.chats by id instead of holding a let-bound copy.
Rename / add-member / leave update the title and members list
without leaving the view.

GlobalChatsView empty hint now reflects the new "+" menu (was
"Tap the magnifier...").

Co-Authored-By: Anton 4.5 &lt;noreply@anthropic.com&gt;
